The National Pension Commission (PenCom) has announced an additional release of N31.97 billion by the Federal Government for the payment of accrued pension rights to 2021 retirees. This is coming after the release of the sum of N16.67 billion on Decemebr 29, 2020, thus bringing the total amount released for payment of the 2021 accrued pension rights to N48.64 billion. The payment is for retirees of Treasury-funded Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs).   NACCIMA: build on telecoms sector gains     Ilorin winners receive prizes in Glo promo     NCS generates N2.2tr revenue in 2021   The Federal Government had earlier settled all arrears of accrued pension rights payments to the verified and enrolled retirees up to December 2020. Findings by the newspaper further revealed that the commission has commenced processing the payments which will begin to hit retirees Retirement Savings Account (RSAs) domiciled with Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) by month end. - Advertisement - Before the payment of N16.67 billion in December last year, the Federal Government total pension liability to retirees was over N100 billion. The Director-General, Mrs Aisha Dahir-Umar is however optimistic that the settlement of the outstanding accrued pension rights is a significant developments, noting that all outstanding payments will be secured from the Federal Government by the Commission.